{"title_page": "1921 Polish Football Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[List of Polish football champions|Polish Football Championship]]\n| season             = 1921\n| dates              = 21 August 1921 \u2013<br />30 October 1921\n| winners            = [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]] (1st title)\n| matches            = 20\n| total goals        = 84\n| league topscorer   = [[J\u00f3zef Ka\u0142u\u017ca]]<br />(9 goals)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.90minut.pl/strona.php?id=rozgrywki_mp_strzelcy |title=Kr\u00f3lowie Strzelc\u00f3w |language=Polish |work=90minut.pl |accessdate=5 May 2015}}</ref>\n| biggest home win   = [[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (1904)|Pogo\u0144]] 7\u20130 [[Warta Pozna\u0144|Warta]]<br />{{nowrap|(16 October 1921)}}\n| biggest away win   = [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a|\u0141KS]] 1\u20136 [[Polonia Warsaw|Polonia]]<br />{{nowrap|(23 October 1921)}}\n| highest scoring    = [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]] 7\u20131 [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a|\u0141KS]]<br />{{nowrap|(28 August 1921)}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wikipasy.pl/1921-08-28_Cracovia_-_%C5%81KS_%C5%81%C3%B3d%C5%BA_7:1 |title=Match report |language=Polish |work=wikipasy.pl |date=7 January 2007 |accessdate=10 December 2016}}</ref>\n| longest wins       = 4 matches<br />[[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]]\n| longest unbeaten   = 8 matches<br />[[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]]\n| longest winless    = 8 matches<br />[[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a|\u0141KS]]\n| longest losses     = 5 matches<br />[[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a|\u0141KS]]\n| highest attendance = 10,000<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305222437fw_/http://goxo.pl/hp-sup-13.pdf |title=Klubowa historia polskiej pi\u0142ki no\u017cnej do 1970 roku/Suplement\u2013Tabele|language=Polish |work=goxo.pl |accessdate=5 March 2016}}</ref><br />[[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]] 2\u20130 [[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (1904)|Pogo\u0144]]<br />{{nowrap|(21 August 1921)}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wikipasy.pl/1921-08-21_Cracovia_-_Pogo%C5%84_Lw%C3%B3w_2:0 |title=Match report |language=Polish |work=wikipasy.pl |date=7 January 2007 |accessdate=19 June 2013}}</ref>\n| prevseason         = [[1920 Polish Football Championship|1920]]\n| nextseason         = [[1922 Polish Football Championship|1922]]\n}}\n[[File:PL Aklasa 1921.jpg|thumb|Five regional A-Classes, whose winners competed in the national championship.]]\n'''1921 Polish Football Championship''' was the 2nd edition of the [[List of Polish football champions|Polish Football Championship]] (Non-League) and 1st completed season ended with the selection of a winner. The championship was decided in final tournament played among five teams ([[Lower Level Football Leagues in Interwar Poland|winners of the regional A-Class championship]]). The champions were [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]], who won their 1st Polish title.\n\n==Competition modus==\nThe final tournament started on 21 August 1921 and concluded on 30 October 1921 (spring-autumn system). The season was played as a [[round-robin tournament]]. The team at the top of the standings won the title. A total of 5 teams participated. Each team played a total of 8 matches, half at home and half away, two games against each other team. Teams received two points for a win and one point for a draw.\n\n==Teams==\n:''Note: Table lists in alphabetical order.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n! Team !! Location !! Venue !! Qualified as\n|-\n| [[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]] || [[Krak\u00f3w]] || [[Marshal J\u00f3zef Pi\u0142sudski Stadium|Stadion Cracovii]] || Krak\u00f3w Regional A-Class Championship winner\n|-\n| [[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] || [[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a]] || Boisko przy ulicy Srebrzy\u0144skiej || \u0141\u00f3d\u017a Regional A-Class Championship winner\n|-\n| [[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (1904)|Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w]] || [[Lviv|Lw\u00f3w]] || Park Sportowy \"Stadion za rogatk\u0105 stryjsk\u0105\" || Lw\u00f3w Regional A-Class Championship winner\n|-\n| [[Polonia Warsaw]] || [[Warsaw]] || Boisko w Parku Sobieskiego na Agrykoli || Warsaw Regional A-Class Championship winner\n|-\n| [[Warta Pozna\u0144]] || [[Pozna\u0144]] || Boisko przy placu Ci\u0119tym || Pozna\u0144 Regional A-Class Championship winner\n|}\n\n==Final tournament table==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|sortable_table=y\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=CRA|name_CRA=[[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]]\n|team2=POL|name_POL=[[Polonia Warsaw]]\n|team3=WAR|name_WAR=[[Warta Pozna\u0144]]\n|team4=PGL|name_PGL=[[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (1904)|Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w]]\n|team5=\u0141KS|name_\u0141KS=[[\u0141KS \u0141\u00f3d\u017a]]\n|win_CRA=7|draw_CRA=1|loss_CRA=0|gf_CRA=31|ga_CRA=7\n|win_POL=5|draw_POL=0|loss_POL=3|gf_POL=13|ga_POL=9\n|win_WAR=3|draw_WAR=2|loss_WAR=3|gf_WAR=14|ga_WAR=24\n|win_PGL=3|draw_PGL=0|loss_PGL=5|gf_PGL=19|ga_PGL=13\n|win_\u0141KS=0|draw_\u0141KS=1|loss_\u0141KS=7|gf_\u0141KS=7|ga_\u0141KS=31\n|update=complete|source=[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesp/polhist.html rsssf.com]\n}}\n\n==Top goalscorers==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Player\n!Club\n!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|1\n|align=\"left\"|{{Flagicon|POL}} [[J\u00f3zef Ka\u0142u\u017ca]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]]\n|rowspan=\"1\"|9\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|2\n|align=\"left\"|{{Flagicon|POL}} [[Wac\u0142aw Kuchar]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w (1904)|Pogo\u0144 Lw\u00f3w]]\n|rowspan=\"1\"|8\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|3\n|align=\"left\"|{{Flagicon|POL}} [[Boles\u0142aw Kotapka]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[KS Cracovia (football)|Cracovia]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|7\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{Flagicon|POL}} [[Marian Einbacher]]\n|align=\"left\"|[[Warta Pozna\u0144]]\n|}\n\n==Medal squads==\n''(Tournament appearances and goals listed in brackets)''\n{| class=\"wikitable\" Width=\"600\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"\n| align=\"center\" width=\"600\" |<span style=\"color:#FF